item.description:
This can be necessary for example for selector like #id &gt; li:visible.
If you will try to do webdriver.find_element_by_css_selector you will get an error message &ldquo;The given selector #id &gt; li:visible is either invalid or does not result in a WebElement.&rdquo;
The workaround is to use jQuery to find element. It can be done with this code (python):
script = &quot;return $('&quot;+selector+&quot;').get(0);&quot; element = webdriver.execute_script(script);
